Great! Let's now define general API information using annotations provided by SpringDoc OpenAPI. This will replace the default Swagger UI title and description with your own custom metadata.
üßæ Step-by-Step: Define General API Info
You‚Äôll use the @OpenAPIDefinition annotation at the main application class level (or a configuration class).

‚úÖ 1. Import Required Annotations
Make sure you import these:

import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.OpenAPIDefinition;
import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.info.Info;
import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.info.Contact;
import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.info.License;

‚úÖ 2. Add Annotation to Your Main Class
Here‚Äôs a complete example:
@OpenAPIDefinition(
    info = @Info(
        title = "User Management API",
        version = "1.0",
        description = "This API allows CRUD operations on users.",
        contact = @Contact(
            name = "Sri Rani Kanaka Ratnam",
            email = "sri.rani@example.com",
            url = "https://your-portfolio.com"
        ),
        license = @License(
            name = "Apache 2.0",
            url = "https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0"
        )
    )
)
@SpringBootApplication
public class UserManagementApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(UserManagementApplication.class, args);
    }
}

üìå What Each Field Means
Field          	Description
title	           The name of your API shown at the top of Swagger UI
version 	        API version (e.g., 1.0, v2)
description	      A short summary of what your API does
contact	          Your name, email, and website (optional)
license	          License info (optional but good for public APIs)

üîç Result in Swagger UI
After restarting your Spring Boot app and visiting:

http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui/index.html

package Net.javaguides.springboot;



import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.ExternalDocumentation;
import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.OpenAPIDefinition;
import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.info.Contact;
import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.info.Info;
import io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.info.License;
import org.modelmapper.ModelMapper;
import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;

@Configuration
@SpringBootApplication
@OpenAPIDefinition(
		info = @Info(
				title = "Spring Boot REST API Documentation",
				description = "Spring Boot REST API Documentation",
				version = "v1.0",
				contact = @Contact(
						name = "Rani",
						email = "Rani@gmail.com",
						url = "https://www.youtube.com"
				),
				license = @License( // ‚úÖ lowercase 'l'
				name = "Spring Boot User",
				url = "https://youtube.com"

				)
		),
		externalDocs = @ExternalDocumentation(
				description = "Spring Boot User Management Documentation",
				url = "https://www.youtube.com/user_management.html"
				)


)

public class SpringbootRestWebservicesApplication {
	@Bean
	public ModelMapper modelMapper(){
		return new ModelMapper();

	}

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		SpringApplication.run(SpringbootRestWebservicesApplication.class, args);
	}

}


